WEBVTT

00:00.405 --> 00:02.005
<i>Lou:</i>
<i>Previously on "Heartland":</i>

00:02.041 --> 00:05.375
Jack: Sheep? Who gave you permission
to bring in a herd of sheep?

00:05.409 --> 00:08.311
There's never been sheep on this
ranch and there never will be.

00:08.346 --> 00:11.581
Lou: Maggie's is for sale?
Oh my gosh.

00:11.616 --> 00:13.416
Jake: You'll find another job.

00:13.484 --> 00:17.687
It wasn't just a job, Maggie's
was a huge part of my life.

00:17.756 --> 00:19.622
Why don't you buy Maggie's,
Lou?

00:19.689 --> 00:22.558
You'd be a great owner
and I could be your manager.

00:22.626 --> 00:24.861
I got a job
on a wild west show.

00:24.895 --> 00:26.295
In Paris?

00:26.930 --> 00:31.333
So they accepted the offer,
and we just bought Maggie's.

00:32.302 --> 00:34.303
Being a manager is a huge job.

00:34.371 --> 00:37.439
For someone who's only
waitressed part-time,

00:37.474 --> 00:38.940
I just,
I don't think you're ready.

00:40.577 --> 00:44.045
♪

00:44.080 --> 00:45.514
Jack:
Oh, will you look at this?

00:45.548 --> 00:46.848
Tim: Oh, come on, I
don't believe it.

00:46.883 --> 00:49.418
What are those sheep doing
way up here?

00:49.452 --> 00:51.653
Jack: I got better
ways to spend my time

00:51.687 --> 00:54.656
than chase down sheep
every time they get out.

00:54.690 --> 00:55.890
Tim: Are you kidding me?

00:55.957 --> 00:58.259
The money we stand to make,
it's worth the time.

00:58.294 --> 00:59.494
Money? What money?

00:59.528 --> 01:01.862
Market's down,
my expenses are up.

01:01.897 --> 01:05.266
Yeah? Well, the guy I bought
'em from was a weekend rancher

01:05.301 --> 01:06.567
who didn't want
the aggravation,

01:06.602 --> 01:08.968
<i>and would sell them</i>
<i>at any price.</i>

01:09.003 --> 01:10.804
What are we talkin'?

01:10.838 --> 01:12.138
Twenty bucks a head.

01:14.141 --> 01:16.476
They're already worth
at least ten times that.

01:16.511 --> 01:18.011
<i>Tim: That's right.</i>

01:18.045 --> 01:21.381
Of course, if you want to get out of the
sheep business, just give me the word.

01:28.422 --> 01:32.090
<i>Amy: Ty, I only told Scott
I would think about it.</i>

01:32.125 --> 01:33.926
Well, he's pretty sure
you'd come around.

01:33.960 --> 01:35.695
Oh, he was wrong.

01:35.729 --> 01:36.995
Do you know
what my schedule is like?

01:37.030 --> 01:38.364
I've got a tonne
of client horses,

01:38.398 --> 01:42.166
and Lou wants me to take some dude
ranch person out on a trail ride.

01:42.201 --> 01:43.635
Don't even open that door.

01:43.669 --> 01:45.437
Ty, just take them away.

01:46.372 --> 01:48.440
[Gate clanks open]

01:50.275 --> 01:52.076
Ty: This is Bobby Jean.

01:53.546 --> 01:55.313
She's a champion cutting horse.

01:55.380 --> 01:56.814
Her owner's really pushing
to get her back in the show ring

01:56.881 --> 01:57.815
as soon as possible.

01:57.849 --> 01:59.282
I'm not even looking.

01:59.317 --> 02:01.151
[Hooves clop]

02:01.219 --> 02:03.286
<i>Ty: Well, you're
missing the best part:</i>

02:03.355 --> 02:05.121
Shiloh.

02:05.156 --> 02:07.458
Really something, isn't he?

02:08.425 --> 02:09.925
Ty, he's so cute.

02:13.464 --> 02:15.165
<i>Ty: So you'll do it?</i>

02:15.199 --> 02:17.234
You know what it's like weaning
a foal this young.

02:17.301 --> 02:19.802
If it's not done right,
there could be severe problems.

02:19.871 --> 02:23.039
He could have weight loss, stress,
<i>immune deficiency issues.</i>

02:23.107 --> 02:24.407
<i>Ty: I know, I know.</i>

02:24.475 --> 02:26.476
That's why Scott needs
your help, Amy.

02:26.510 --> 02:29.178
The owner,
he's, he's old school.

02:29.246 --> 02:30.445
He's a bit of a jerk.

02:30.513 --> 02:32.181
He wanted to split them up;

02:32.249 --> 02:35.050
Dump the foal off at the clinic
and leave us with the fallout.

02:37.354 --> 02:39.788
Well, how long would I have?

02:39.856 --> 02:42.258
The mare has to be back home
day after tomorrow.

02:42.325 --> 02:44.025
[Sighs]

02:45.494 --> 02:49.197
Lou: Okay, Georgie, we only have a
couple of hours to get everything ready.

02:49.265 --> 02:53.001
Georgie: Yeah, yeah, but I don't get
it, why are we opening up early

02:53.035 --> 02:55.403
and what's so important
about this Nicole person?

02:55.437 --> 02:56.637
Everything.

02:56.671 --> 02:58.406
In New York,
she graduated top of our class.

02:58.473 --> 03:00.507
She got the best job
right out of school.

03:00.574 --> 03:04.544
She's super smart, super
committed, super ambitious.

03:04.578 --> 03:07.281
Georgie: She sounds like a
super pain in the butt.

03:07.348 --> 03:09.749
She is, actually, but she's
also a really good friend.

03:11.319 --> 03:14.254
Okay. And I wanna pitch her on
this place as a corporate retreat.

03:14.322 --> 03:15.622
A what?

03:15.689 --> 03:17.790
You know, trail rides,
team building.

03:17.857 --> 03:19.358
It could be
a real game changer,

03:19.393 --> 03:21.527
so we're all pulling together
to make it happen.

03:21.561 --> 03:23.996
And here is a list
of chores...

03:24.031 --> 03:25.798
And don't forget
to sweep the porch, okay?

03:25.865 --> 03:28.500
You're the best! Thank you.

03:28.535 --> 03:30.569
I'll be back soon.

03:31.704 --> 03:32.804
Amy: I still don't
know about this, Ty.

03:32.838 --> 03:36.041
I mean, a week, maybe,
but two days?

03:36.075 --> 03:39.911
Well, Scott had to do a lot of fancy
footwork to even get you that.

03:39.946 --> 03:41.146
Look at them, though.

03:41.213 --> 03:43.214
<i>They're inseparable.</i>

03:43.249 --> 03:44.249
<i>Ty:</i>
<i>If you don't give it a shot,</i>

03:44.283 --> 03:46.918
it's gonna be a lot worse
for them.

03:48.286 --> 03:50.988
Well,
they are settling in okay.

03:51.957 --> 03:53.123
[Sheep bleat]

03:54.725 --> 03:56.260
Oh, great.

03:56.294 --> 03:57.894
Let's get them
before grandpa sees them.

03:57.929 --> 04:00.297
Or has another heart attack.

04:00.332 --> 04:01.498
Amy: Go! Shoo! Come on, sheep!

04:01.532 --> 04:03.067
Ty: Push them into
the corner there!

04:03.101 --> 04:03.900
You got those ones?!

04:03.935 --> 04:05.001
Amy: Yup.

04:06.403 --> 04:07.903
Ty: Yeah, run!

04:09.039 --> 04:11.040
Nice!

04:11.075 --> 04:12.908
[Door shuts]

04:12.943 --> 04:16.846
Okay, I have got a big list
of stuff I need,

04:16.880 --> 04:18.814
but you can start me off
with a low-fat latte.

04:18.849 --> 04:20.382
And hello to you, too.

04:20.416 --> 04:23.151
The hello was implied,
mallory.

04:24.220 --> 04:26.388
What's going on?
Where is everybody?

04:26.422 --> 04:27.755
We ran out of coffee.

04:27.790 --> 04:29.057
We ran out?

04:29.092 --> 04:31.693
Okay, mallory,
we can't run out of coffee.

04:31.727 --> 04:33.728
Maggie's is all about coffee.

04:33.762 --> 04:38.132
Believe me, I know, and if I were
manager I would have put in the order,

04:38.166 --> 04:41.502
but I'm just the waitress and
waitresses can't place orders.

04:41.536 --> 04:43.104
What else do we need?

04:43.138 --> 04:46.207
Basically, all the stuff
on this list,

04:46.241 --> 04:48.075
<i>but it's really hard for me</i>
<i>to say for sure</i>

04:48.110 --> 04:50.411
'cause it's not really
my department.

04:51.346 --> 04:54.815
This is exactly why I didn't
give you the manager job.

04:54.849 --> 04:58.952
And this is exactly why I'm not doing
the job you didn't hire me to do.

05:00.788 --> 05:02.155
[Car rumbles up]

05:07.862 --> 05:10.162
Hi. Um, are you Nicole?

05:10.196 --> 05:11.163
I am.

05:11.197 --> 05:12.532
You must be... Georgina?

05:12.599 --> 05:13.799
Georgie. Right.

05:15.235 --> 05:17.302
Georgie: So, can I help
you with your luggage?

05:17.370 --> 05:19.572
Nicole:
Oh, I think I can handle it.

05:19.606 --> 05:24.309
This trip was sort of a spur of the
moment, last minute kind of deal.

05:25.277 --> 05:28.179
Wow! The place looks,
uh, looks fantastic.

05:28.247 --> 05:30.615
Which, which cabin am I in?

05:30.650 --> 05:31.716
Oh, this one.

05:31.784 --> 05:33.852
Oh, perfect.
Same as last time.

05:33.920 --> 05:35.787
Georgie:
Watch out for the horse cra-p.

05:35.855 --> 05:36.788
Nicole: Oh my...

05:36.856 --> 05:38.690
Are you kidding me?

05:38.758 --> 05:40.224
[Scoffs]

05:40.292 --> 05:41.825
Why didn't you warn me?

05:41.893 --> 05:43.126
I tried.

05:44.095 --> 05:45.328
[Groaning]

05:45.363 --> 05:48.799
All right, wait, wait, wait.
Just let me, okay?

05:48.867 --> 05:50.500
Oh, just get it off.

05:50.569 --> 05:51.969
I know, I'm trying.

05:52.037 --> 05:53.837
I've got it, I've got it.

05:54.806 --> 05:56.440
Oh.

05:56.507 --> 05:58.007
Okay, what do you want me
to do with them?

05:58.075 --> 06:01.044
Just throw it away,
as far as possible.

06:06.550 --> 06:09.586
Are you sure
this is the right cabin?

06:10.554 --> 06:13.889
You think this is bad,
you should see the others.

06:13.957 --> 06:16.725
Hmm. I'm going to,
I'm going to change my shoes

06:16.793 --> 06:20.829
and then I'm going to help you
fix this place up.

06:23.833 --> 06:24.833
Whoa.

06:28.137 --> 06:29.570
Georgie.

06:31.272 --> 06:33.040
Georgie,
what have you been doing?

06:33.108 --> 06:37.812
This place is a disaster and someone
tracked crap all over the deck.

06:37.846 --> 06:39.714
Nicole is going to be here
in any second.

06:39.748 --> 06:42.683
Georgie: Lou. Lou: No, no, Georgie, you
have no idea what we're dealing with.

06:42.751 --> 06:45.952
If this place is not perfect,
she is going to turn around

06:45.987 --> 06:48.221
and storm out of here
like some park Avenue princess.

06:48.288 --> 06:50.223
Lou, would you-

06:52.893 --> 06:53.927
Nicole!

06:55.295 --> 06:57.030
It is so good to see you.

06:57.064 --> 06:59.599
You know what, Lou?
You're right.

07:02.602 --> 07:05.570
But obviously it's not.

07:06.906 --> 07:11.710
Sorry, I'm going to storm out of
here, just like you said I would.

07:12.646 --> 07:13.979
Little warning.

07:14.914 --> 07:22.687
♪

07:22.689 --> 07:30.294
♪

07:30.328 --> 07:32.896
♪ And at the break of day

07:32.930 --> 07:37.634
♪ you sank into your dreams

07:37.669 --> 07:38.935
♪ you dreamer

07:38.970 --> 07:41.504
♪ oh, oh, oh...

07:41.539 --> 07:44.107
♪ You dreamer

07:45.777 --> 07:50.680
♪ you dreamer

07:50.705 --> 07:55.951
<b><u><font color="#96f171">Sync & corrections by no1
www.Addic7ed.Com</font></u></b>

07:55.952 --> 07:57.753
Lou: Nicole, just wait.

07:57.788 --> 08:00.489
Nicole: Don't even bother trying to
sweet talk me into staying, Lou.

08:00.523 --> 08:02.624
I'm calling a cab.

08:02.659 --> 08:05.727
Lou: Okay, well, you know,
that's good, that's a relief.

08:05.761 --> 08:09.064
At least you're not going to, I don't
know, drown yourself or swim for freedom.

08:09.098 --> 08:10.498
Just, just stay back,
Lou, okay?

08:10.532 --> 08:12.366
I'm just, I'm going to call,
I swear.

08:12.434 --> 08:15.136
Okay, do it, but I
should warn you,

08:15.171 --> 08:16.905
the cell reception
is pretty spotty out here

08:16.972 --> 08:19.941
so you might just wanna
dive right in.

08:19.975 --> 08:22.042
Just watch out for leeches.

08:25.546 --> 08:27.581
<i>Nicole: Okay, yeah.</i>

08:27.615 --> 08:29.682
I actually, I miss this, Lou.

08:29.750 --> 08:33.152
You know, having someone
call me out on my ocd bs.

08:33.187 --> 08:35.654
Yeah, just like the good
ol' days, except back then

08:35.688 --> 08:37.356
we only did it
behind your back.

08:40.126 --> 08:42.628
I was just jokin-Nicole!

08:42.696 --> 08:45.597
Okay, listen, I'm really
sorry about the cabin.

08:45.664 --> 08:48.166
I'm gonna fix it up,
it'll be okay.

08:48.234 --> 08:50.802
It's not the cabin.

08:50.870 --> 08:52.337
[Sniffles]

08:52.404 --> 08:54.172
Well, is there anything
I can do?

08:57.176 --> 08:59.477
Georgie: And it took Lou an
hour to get her to stop crying.

08:59.545 --> 09:00.845
Amy: [Groans]

09:02.848 --> 09:06.016
<i>Georgie: Oh, is that them?!
Look how cute he is!</i>

09:06.084 --> 09:07.451
<i>How long are they staying?</i>

09:07.518 --> 09:10.221
Just a couple of days, so if you're going
to help me with this weaning process,

09:10.288 --> 09:12.623
you have to promise
not to get too attached.

09:12.657 --> 09:14.458
<i>Georgie: Okay, I promise.</i>

09:14.525 --> 09:15.992
When do we start?

09:16.060 --> 09:17.426
<i>Amy: Well, you see
foals like shiloh,</i>

09:17.494 --> 09:19.595
<i>their main source of food</i>
<i>is their mother's milk,</i>

09:19.630 --> 09:22.766
but that can't go on forever,
so we need to separate them.

09:22.833 --> 09:24.067
You're taking him away
from his mother?

09:24.135 --> 09:25.434
That's so mean!

09:25.502 --> 09:27.070
Amy: Well, yes, it can be,

09:27.104 --> 09:28.738
<i>but we're going to make sure</i>
<i>we do it right,</i>

09:28.806 --> 09:32.941
<i>and nice and gentle</i> so that neither
of them get too stressed out.

09:33.009 --> 09:35.577
All right, let's back up
and give them some space.

09:37.446 --> 09:38.680
[Snorting softly]

09:44.921 --> 09:46.755
<i>Georgie: Foal's eating
the mom's food.</i>

09:46.790 --> 09:47.689
<i>Is that okay?</i>

09:47.723 --> 09:49.090
Amy: That's really good.

09:49.124 --> 09:52.559
That means we can start giving him some
grain along with his milk substitute.

09:52.627 --> 09:54.095
<i>[Amy chuckles]</i>

09:55.063 --> 09:56.197
[Neighing]

09:57.332 --> 09:58.532
<i>Look at that.</i>

09:58.566 --> 10:00.001
See, he's keeping a close eye
on his mother

10:00.035 --> 10:02.469
but he's looking
at the other horses.

10:02.537 --> 10:03.937
<i>He's only been here</i>
<i>a few hours</i>

10:04.005 --> 10:06.072
and he's already beginning
to socialize.

10:06.140 --> 10:10.043
<i>But he can't do that</i> if he's stuck
to his mother's side all the time.

10:10.077 --> 10:12.145
[Bleating loudly]

10:14.782 --> 10:16.349
[Startled whinny]

10:16.383 --> 10:18.584
<i>Georgie: Oh no, Amy, look!
They're scaring them.</i>

10:18.652 --> 10:21.921
<i>Amy: Those stupid sheep,</i> they're
gonna ruin everything. Come on.

10:21.988 --> 10:23.022
Okay, come on, sheep, get out!

10:23.056 --> 10:25.124
Georgie: Shoo! Shoo!

10:26.927 --> 10:28.260
Oh good, grandpa.

10:28.328 --> 10:29.761
You know I am trying to wean
a foal out there, right,

10:29.796 --> 10:31.596
and these sheep are really
getting in the way.

10:31.631 --> 10:35.367
Don't talk to me. You talk to your father,
he's the one who brought 'em here.

10:35.401 --> 10:36.567
I thought you two
were partners?

10:36.601 --> 10:39.337
Well, that depends on
how you define partners.

10:39.371 --> 10:42.073
According to him,
we're fifty-fifty.

10:42.107 --> 10:44.575
He bought the sheep, but I've
been paying for everything else

10:44.609 --> 10:46.277
in more ways than one.

10:46.312 --> 10:48.779
Okay, so let's just get rid
of them, right now!

10:48.814 --> 10:50.681
Here's the situation.

10:50.716 --> 10:54.617
The longer those sheep are
here, the more money I spend.

10:54.652 --> 10:58.222
Now the more money I spend,
the bigger my share is.

10:58.256 --> 11:02.525
Now, when I add labour,
vet bills, and aggravation

11:02.560 --> 11:06.196
to a carefully calculated
grazing fee,

11:06.231 --> 11:08.965
your dad's fifty percent
will have shrunk so small

11:08.999 --> 11:11.100
I'll practically own
the whole flock myself.

11:11.134 --> 11:12.601
Grandpa, you hate sheep!

11:12.635 --> 11:16.973
I sure do, and when they're mine
I'm gonna sell them so fast

11:17.007 --> 11:19.175
it'll make your head spin.

11:19.209 --> 11:22.478
That'll teach him to dump
those sheep on my land.

11:24.380 --> 11:28.416
You should have seen the look on Lou's
face when I told her about the coffee.

11:28.450 --> 11:30.451
I thought you wanted
to be manager?

11:30.519 --> 11:32.153
Yeah, but according to Lou,

11:32.221 --> 11:35.823
I don't have the maturity
or the experience to do so.

11:35.858 --> 11:37.525
So what are you gonna do?

11:37.559 --> 11:40.194
Well, from now on,
it's work to rule.

11:40.228 --> 11:44.731
If she wants a manager, she can hire
me to do it, or pay someone else.

11:44.766 --> 11:46.566
You sure you really
want this job?

11:46.634 --> 11:50.104
I mean, most people would try to
show their boss they can handle it.

11:51.039 --> 11:55.376
You mean, act like a manager and
she'll see me as a manager.

11:55.410 --> 11:57.476
Yeah, but you're basically
doing the exact opposite,

11:57.511 --> 12:01.414
so it's like
you don't want the job, right?

12:01.481 --> 12:04.717
Oh my gosh,
you are absolutely right!

12:04.751 --> 12:06.519
When did you get so smart?

12:07.487 --> 12:10.423
I've always been smart,
you just never noticed it.

12:13.592 --> 12:15.627
Maybe too smart.

12:18.197 --> 12:19.331
Hey, dad.

12:19.399 --> 12:23.802
Hi, Amy. What can I do for ya?

12:23.869 --> 12:25.503
If you really want to do
something for me,

12:25.571 --> 12:28.505
you could move those sheep that
are at heartland out here.

12:30.008 --> 12:33.377
I'm keeping things going while your
grandfather's waltzing around Arizona.

12:33.445 --> 12:34.912
He was not waltzing, okay?

12:34.980 --> 12:37.081
He was recovering
from a heart attack.

12:37.149 --> 12:40.151
Yeah, well, that's why
I let him in on the deal.

12:40.218 --> 12:43.421
High profits, low maintenance,
perfect for the golden ager.

12:43.488 --> 12:45.521
And I threw in a dog.

12:45.589 --> 12:47.723
And what thanks do I get?
I get nothing but grief.

12:47.791 --> 12:50.060
You know, I am sure
that you meant well, okay?

12:50.127 --> 12:53.129
But I cannot work with those sheep
around, so just load them in a trailer

12:53.197 --> 12:55.265
and bring them up here.

12:55.299 --> 12:58.034
Take a look around.
This is prime cattle country.

12:58.102 --> 13:01.770
You think I'm gonna let a
bunch of sheep eat my grass?

13:04.907 --> 13:08.910
Nicole: Wow! It's so great
you bought this place, Lou!

13:08.945 --> 13:11.347
You know, my grandmother used
to have a cafe just like it.

13:11.381 --> 13:13.015
Lou: Really? You never told me.

13:13.049 --> 13:14.416
Yeah, in high school.

13:14.484 --> 13:18.552
I spent every summer there just
working in the kitchen, waitressing.

13:18.587 --> 13:22.623
Mallory: Enjoy. Hi, guys, how're
the first few bites tasting?

13:22.657 --> 13:23.724
Great.

13:23.792 --> 13:25.293
Lou: Whoa!

13:25.327 --> 13:26.894
Mallory: Bye.

13:26.928 --> 13:28.229
[Phone rings]

13:29.431 --> 13:31.499
Hello, Maggie's.

13:31.533 --> 13:33.867
Yes, I need you guys
to double our order.

13:33.901 --> 13:35.902
Okay, just one second.

13:37.372 --> 13:39.139
Hi, Lou, I'm so happy
you could drop by.

13:39.173 --> 13:42.442
I placed in these orders, I got the
new menus, next week's special,

13:42.510 --> 13:44.277
and the resumes
for the waitress job.

13:44.312 --> 13:45.979
Okay.

13:46.014 --> 13:47.414
Hi, sorry about that.

13:48.515 --> 13:50.649
Okay, thank you. Bye.

13:50.683 --> 13:53.785
Um, mallory,
you remember Nicole?

13:53.820 --> 13:55.388
Nicole, of course.

13:55.422 --> 13:58.590
Let me guess,
two non-fat lattes?

13:58.625 --> 14:00.692
Uh, that sounds great.

14:00.727 --> 14:02.428
I'll get those right away.

14:02.462 --> 14:06.498
Lou, I wanted to apologize
about this morning.

14:06.532 --> 14:10.268
I just remembered why I pushed you into
getting Maggie's in the first place.

14:10.302 --> 14:13.405
Because you lost your job and
you were hoping to get it back?

14:13.439 --> 14:17.675
No, because Maggie's is more
than a cafe and a tack shop.

14:17.709 --> 14:23.380
It's a place to go, to meet with
old friends, to make new friends.

14:23.415 --> 14:28.118
It's a place where you can feel
a part of something.

14:28.153 --> 14:32.056
Anyway, I'm just happy that I
could help make it all possible.

14:33.791 --> 14:37.326
Oh, wow, you really lucked
out with your manager.

14:37.361 --> 14:40.063
Mallory?
She's not the manager.

14:40.997 --> 14:43.332
She wants the job,
but I told her she wasn't ready,

14:43.367 --> 14:46.169
so she's just trying
to impress me.

14:46.236 --> 14:49.838
Well, I was managing my
grandmother's cafe at her age.

14:49.873 --> 14:52.240
Yeah, but mallory is not you.

14:53.209 --> 14:59.747
Here we go, two of Maggie's special
non-fat lattes, voted best in Hudson.

14:59.782 --> 15:02.484
Anything else I can get
for you two?

15:02.552 --> 15:03.985
[Lou sighs]

15:04.053 --> 15:06.388
Okay, mallory, you win.

15:06.456 --> 15:08.189
You want the job, you got it.

15:08.223 --> 15:10.624
Yes! You won't regret this.

15:12.994 --> 15:14.895
[Sighs]

15:19.692 --> 15:21.960
Amy: All right, I'm just
gonna hang on to her.

15:22.028 --> 15:22.994
Georgie: What do I do?

15:23.062 --> 15:26.631
I want you to back away and show
shiloh that that grain in the bucket

15:26.699 --> 15:28.433
is way more important
than his mom.

15:28.467 --> 15:30.368
Okay. Here, shiloh!

15:30.436 --> 15:31.536
Come get it!

15:31.570 --> 15:33.871
Come on,
I've got something tasty.

15:33.939 --> 15:34.905
<i>Over here!</i>

15:34.940 --> 15:36.340
Come and get it.

15:41.980 --> 15:43.347
[Neighing]

15:44.549 --> 15:45.615
[Laughing]

15:47.885 --> 15:50.586
Looks like he wants a buddy
more than food.

15:50.654 --> 15:51.921
<i>Oh, he likes pogey.</i>

15:53.891 --> 15:55.291
Sheep: [Bleating]

15:55.359 --> 15:58.061
Amy: Oh no! No, no, no!
Not again! Not again!

15:58.128 --> 15:59.562
<i>Georgie: Shiloh!</i>

15:59.629 --> 16:00.997
<i>Amy, what do I do?</i>

16:02.666 --> 16:04.499
Amy:
Those sheep have got to go.

16:04.533 --> 16:08.036
Georgie, can you just deal
with them, please?

16:08.104 --> 16:10.305
Hey, you, get out of here.

16:10.340 --> 16:11.740
Beat it! Scram!

16:11.774 --> 16:13.909
[Claps] Go on!

16:13.943 --> 16:15.110
[Bleating]

16:15.178 --> 16:16.811
Uh-oh! Whoa!

16:17.847 --> 16:19.248
Agghhh!

16:19.315 --> 16:20.381
[Bleating]

16:22.117 --> 16:27.088
One coffee, no milk, no
sugar, nothing on the side.

16:28.023 --> 16:30.258
So no more working to rule?

16:30.292 --> 16:33.527
Yeah,
I realized you were right.

16:34.529 --> 16:38.464
The only thing I was proving is
that I wasn't manager material.

16:38.532 --> 16:40.400
And besides, who wants to spend
their whole gap year

16:40.434 --> 16:45.238
being a waitress at Maggie's
when they can be manager?

16:45.306 --> 16:46.873
You got the job?

16:46.941 --> 16:49.009
Mallory: Yeah!
Man: Bye, mallory.

16:50.544 --> 16:52.011
What's wrong?

16:52.045 --> 16:54.280
I mean it was your idea.
Aren't you happy for me?

16:54.314 --> 16:55.948
Yeah, of course,

16:57.984 --> 17:00.352
but there are other options.

17:00.387 --> 17:02.054
Such as?

17:02.122 --> 17:06.625
Travel, see the world,
stuff like that.

17:06.659 --> 17:09.727
But if you're happy,
I'm happy.

17:11.829 --> 17:13.231
Gotta go.

17:17.636 --> 17:19.737
[Door opens and clicks shut]

17:21.606 --> 17:22.906
I don't care
how much it costs,

17:22.942 --> 17:25.208
I've gotta get those sheep
trucked out of here now.

17:26.377 --> 17:28.211
Oh, really?

17:28.246 --> 17:31.648
Okay. Well, no, that's fine.
Thank you.

17:31.682 --> 17:32.950
[Frustrated groan]

17:32.984 --> 17:34.952
What's the problem?
Can't they do it?

17:34.986 --> 17:37.554
Oh, they can do it -
next Wednesday.

17:37.588 --> 17:39.456
I've only got until tomorrow.

17:39.490 --> 17:41.390
Hmm. You know what?

17:41.891 --> 17:44.827
Yeah, we're gonna herd them
out of here ourselves.

17:44.861 --> 17:47.563
We can take them up across big
river, up to dad's lease land.

17:47.597 --> 17:49.631
That should only take
a couple hours, right?

17:49.666 --> 17:51.100
When do we start?

17:51.168 --> 17:53.102
[Sighs] Right about now.

17:53.136 --> 17:55.404
[Hooves clop]

17:55.472 --> 17:56.904
Amy: Oh no.

17:56.939 --> 17:57.939
Georgie: "Oh no" what?

17:57.974 --> 18:00.308
I forgot about the trail ride.

18:00.343 --> 18:03.044
Lou: Hey, Amy! You look
like you're all set.

18:03.079 --> 18:03.878
Amy: Yeah.

18:03.912 --> 18:05.046
You remember Nicole?

18:05.114 --> 18:06.081
Amy: Hey, Nicole.

18:06.148 --> 18:07.715
Nicole:
Hey! How's it going, Amy?

18:07.783 --> 18:09.117
Amy: Great. Good.

18:09.185 --> 18:10.618
Can I talk to you
for one second?

18:10.686 --> 18:12.152
Uh, sure, yeah.
I'll be right back.

18:12.187 --> 18:13.387
Nicole: Yeah.

18:14.322 --> 18:15.722
Lou: What's up?

18:15.756 --> 18:18.125
<i>Amy: Well, I have to talk
to you about something.</i>

18:18.159 --> 18:19.559
[Chuckles]

18:20.528 --> 18:21.728
Lou: Amy, what is it?
What's wrong?

18:21.762 --> 18:24.465
Nothing. It's just I don't have time
to go on a trail ride right now.

18:24.499 --> 18:25.866
I've got to do something
with these sheep.

18:25.900 --> 18:28.334
No, no, Amy, you promised me, and
Nicole, she came all the way.

18:28.402 --> 18:30.703
I know, I know, but Lou, I
am trying to wean a foal

18:30.770 --> 18:32.472
and with these sheep around
it's not gonna happen.

18:32.539 --> 18:34.640
Well, then ask grandpa
to move them, or dad.

18:34.708 --> 18:36.075
You think I haven't tried?

18:36.143 --> 18:39.278
Dad says it's grandpa's responsibility,
and he won't even lift a finger,

18:39.313 --> 18:40.646
<i>and then grandpa</i>
<i>has suddenly decided</i>

18:40.714 --> 18:42.348
<i>that he's determined</i>
<i>to keep them here.</i>

18:42.416 --> 18:43.416
What?

18:43.450 --> 18:48.586
Lou, this foal's health is at risk,
and Scott's depending on me. Please?

18:48.654 --> 18:50.422
Lou: [Sighs]

18:50.490 --> 18:52.757
Nicole: Hey, Lou, you know
I don't really need to go

18:52.791 --> 18:54.359
on a trail ride.
I mean there's-

18:54.427 --> 18:56.728
actually, you know, we aren't
gonna do the trail ride,

18:56.795 --> 18:58.930
but we are gonna do something
that's way better.

18:58.998 --> 19:00.998
<i>It's like a full Western</i>
<i>experience.</i>

19:01.033 --> 19:02.233
And you know what,
I'll come too.

19:02.300 --> 19:03.901
It'll be great.

19:03.968 --> 19:06.170
Okay, good.

19:07.972 --> 19:11.108
Ready? Let's move 'em out!

19:12.677 --> 19:14.711
[Hooves clop]

19:19.550 --> 19:21.217
[Gate rattles open]

19:21.285 --> 19:23.219
[Bleating]

19:23.287 --> 19:24.620
<i>Lou: Let's go!</i>

19:24.688 --> 19:26.122
[Bleating]

19:27.091 --> 19:28.491
<i>[Dog barks]</i>

19:28.559 --> 19:30.026
[Bleating]

19:30.061 --> 19:31.761
<i>Lou: Come on, sheep!</i>

19:31.795 --> 19:32.761
<i>Georgie: Come on, sheep!</i>

19:32.795 --> 19:35.130
Lou: Let's go, sheep, come on.

19:35.198 --> 19:36.631
<i>I'll follow right behind you.</i>

19:36.699 --> 19:38.300
Nicole: Okay.

19:38.368 --> 19:40.135
<i>Come on, sheep!</i>

19:41.071 --> 19:43.138
All right, ladies,
let's bring 'em out.

19:43.206 --> 19:44.339
<i>Lou; Come on, sheep, let's go!</i>

19:44.407 --> 19:46.942
<i>Amy: Come on, sheep,
get up there!</i>

19:47.009 --> 19:48.043
Let's go!

19:48.077 --> 19:50.445
Amy: Come on, let's go!

19:50.479 --> 19:52.380
Come on, sheep! Come on!

19:52.414 --> 19:55.349
Georgie: Come on!
Lou: Let's go!

19:56.091 --> 19:57.167
[Unhappy customer chatter]
Where is our order?

19:58.056 --> 20:00.457
Mal, I gotta run.

20:00.492 --> 20:04.428
Okay, eight seventy-five, from ten...
Yup, close enough.

20:06.130 --> 20:08.799
Hey! Hey... Look who it is.

20:08.833 --> 20:11.968
Oh, it's my- I've got
her, I've got her.

20:12.003 --> 20:15.505
I'm capable of sitting
with a child on my lap.

20:16.473 --> 20:19.108
Oh yeah, if you're so capable,
why is everybody asking me

20:19.176 --> 20:20.577
to get rid of these sheep
for ya?

20:20.611 --> 20:23.012
Well, 'cause they know I'm
doing all the heavy lifting.

20:23.046 --> 20:25.381
Heavy lifting? Oh, come on.

20:25.416 --> 20:29.351
I'm not the bad guy, Jack, those
sheep are worth money in the bank.

20:31.821 --> 20:33.955
Mallory: [Gasps] Oh my gosh!
She swallowed it!

20:33.989 --> 20:35.324
Tim: Just, just...
Mallory: She swallowed a penny!

20:35.358 --> 20:37.593
Okay, come here, honey,
come here, come here.

20:37.627 --> 20:38.727
W-what are you doing?

20:38.761 --> 20:39.994
Tim: I'm gonna do
some first aid.

20:40.062 --> 20:41.896
Don't even think about it.
Mallory, call 9-1-1.

20:41.931 --> 20:45.066
Tim: No we don't have time for 9-1-1,
Jack, let's get her to the hospital.

20:45.101 --> 20:46.300
Let me see now.

20:46.302 --> 20:48.068
Mallory: Hello? Hello?
Emergency services.

20:48.103 --> 20:49.069
Ty: Hey guys, what's up?

20:49.104 --> 20:50.438
Well, Katie swallowed a penny.

20:50.505 --> 20:51.772
Tim: So make a hole, we
gotta get to the hospital.

20:51.806 --> 20:53.005
Whoa, whoa. Is she breathing?

20:53.040 --> 20:54.241
She looks fine.

20:54.275 --> 20:55.875
Tim:
She swallowed a penny, Jack.

20:55.909 --> 20:57.210
Jack:
Mallory, tell them to hurry.

20:57.245 --> 20:58.678
Ty: This happened to a
beagle at the clinic once.

20:58.713 --> 21:01.648
If she's not choking, then the
best thing to do is just wait.

21:01.682 --> 21:05.184
Well, thank you, Dr. borden,
except wait, you're not a doctor.

21:05.219 --> 21:08.054
You're not even a med student,
you're a vet student.

21:08.088 --> 21:09.588
<i>So move, we're leaving!</i>

21:09.623 --> 21:10.889
Tim!

21:10.957 --> 21:13.125
She swallowed a penny;
There's only one way out.

21:13.159 --> 21:14.926
Wait, stop! Ty's right.

21:14.961 --> 21:16.629
Emergency services concurs.

21:16.663 --> 21:19.398
If there's no obstruction,
let nature take its course.

21:19.432 --> 21:20.733
Jack: Well, that's a relief.
Ty: Thank you.

21:20.800 --> 21:21.634
Thank you.

21:21.668 --> 21:22.668
Hmm.

21:22.736 --> 21:23.669
<i>Tim: It's okay, we'll wait.</i>

21:23.737 --> 21:25.737
Lou: Good dog. Move 'em up!

21:25.771 --> 21:26.704
Amy: Keep on movin'!

21:26.739 --> 21:29.307
<i>Georgie: Move up, sheep!</i>

21:30.309 --> 21:32.577
<i>Come on! This way!</i>

21:32.645 --> 21:34.245
<i>Amy: Good goin', Georgie!</i>

21:34.313 --> 21:36.614
[Dog barks, sheep bleat]

21:36.682 --> 21:39.016
Nicole: Whoa! Easy, easy.

21:39.084 --> 21:40.251
[Bleating]

21:40.318 --> 21:41.685
Lou: Are you okay there?

21:41.753 --> 21:45.054
Nicole: Uh, I don't know.
Georgie: This way!

21:45.122 --> 21:46.690
Nicole: Whoa, stop.

21:46.758 --> 21:49.192
Lou: All right, loosen up on the
reins and stop kicking him.

21:49.260 --> 21:50.761
Well, he's not stopping.

21:50.828 --> 21:52.462
Hey, whoa! What's he doing?

21:52.497 --> 21:54.798
Lou: You know what? Amy and Georgie
have the sheep under control...

21:54.832 --> 21:56.499
<i>Nicole: Okay, whoa! Whoa!</i>

21:56.533 --> 21:58.867
Lou: Why don't we just take
a breather, lean back,

21:58.902 --> 21:59.935
and let the horses
calm down a little.

22:00.003 --> 22:03.272
Nicole:
Whoa, whoa, whoa. Whoa!

22:03.340 --> 22:05.408
Easy! Whoa.

22:05.475 --> 22:07.576
Lou: I got him, I got him.

22:07.644 --> 22:09.779
All right, you good? Hop off.

22:09.846 --> 22:12.047
Nicole: Oh! Thank God.

22:12.115 --> 22:13.448
Lou: Are you okay?

22:13.482 --> 22:16.083
Yeah, I'm going to be
walking funny for about a week.

22:16.151 --> 22:18.453
You're doing great.

22:18.521 --> 22:20.254
You know, at least you can
tell everyone at work

22:20.323 --> 22:22.757
that you went on
a real sheep drive.

22:22.825 --> 22:24.426
Maybe you could even
mention it to your boss,

22:24.493 --> 22:25.627
you know, tell her
how great it would be

22:25.661 --> 22:26.894
for all your coworkers
to come out here.

22:26.962 --> 22:30.230
Yeah, Lou, it's great, except
I'm not going back to work.

22:30.298 --> 22:31.432
What?

22:31.499 --> 22:34.301
I don't have a job
to go back to.

22:37.806 --> 22:39.640
That's it, honey, concentrate.

22:39.708 --> 22:40.674
[Katie moans]

22:40.742 --> 22:42.909
Come on, honey, you can do it.

22:42.944 --> 22:45.211
You know, I'm surprised you two aren't
out with Amy and Lou, right now.

22:45.278 --> 22:47.780
What are you talkin' about?

22:47.848 --> 22:49.014
You don't know?

22:49.082 --> 22:50.383
They're moving the sheep
out to the lease land.

22:50.451 --> 22:52.485
They're probably in the
foothills right about now.

22:52.519 --> 22:54.487
I knew they were up
to something.

22:54.555 --> 22:56.456
Mallory: Wow, that sounds
pretty bad, you guys,

22:56.523 --> 22:59.191
just leaving the girls
to do all the work?

22:59.226 --> 23:01.926
Yeah, I thought
they were your sheep?

23:01.961 --> 23:05.330
Well, if I'd have known, I'd
have done something about it.

23:05.365 --> 23:07.399
Well, you might still
have a chance.

23:07.433 --> 23:09.300
Amy's great with horses,
but I don't know about sheep.

23:09.335 --> 23:11.069
She might not even make it
there with them.

23:11.103 --> 23:12.537
So where are you going now?

23:12.605 --> 23:16.674
It's okay, Jack, you just rest
easy and I'll handle this.

23:22.146 --> 23:24.314
Can you handle Katie
for a couple hours?

23:24.349 --> 23:25.282
Yeah, I can watch her.

23:25.350 --> 23:26.950
Good.

23:26.985 --> 23:28.586
Okay.

23:30.154 --> 23:32.489
<i>Lou: So you lost your license?</i>

23:32.523 --> 23:34.257
Well, it's been
temporarily revoked,

23:34.291 --> 23:38.795
and I've been suspended pending the
results of an investigation by the sec.

23:38.829 --> 23:40.663
And what exactly
are they investigating?

23:40.698 --> 23:42.766
You know, the usual,
cooking the books,

23:42.800 --> 23:44.901
insider trading,
pump and dump schemes.

23:44.935 --> 23:47.804
But you weren't involved with
any of that, I mean, were you?

23:47.838 --> 23:50.972
Of course not,
but I heard rumours,

23:51.007 --> 23:53.675
enough so that I probably should
have known that they were true.

23:53.710 --> 23:55.611
And just knowing about it
makes you a criminal?

23:55.645 --> 23:58.313
No. Knowing about it and not
doing anything to stop it

23:58.347 --> 24:00.649
makes me guilty by omission.

24:00.683 --> 24:05.486
And that's kinda why I'm here, Lou, to
just sort of prep me for my appearance

24:05.554 --> 24:08.222
before the commission.

24:08.256 --> 24:11.191
The problem is,
if I tell the truth,

24:11.226 --> 24:15.430
I'll never work in
the financial industry again.

24:16.665 --> 24:17.998
[Trunk rumbles]

24:18.867 --> 24:20.434
Where do you think
you're going?

24:20.468 --> 24:22.335
Amy and Lou need help.

24:22.369 --> 24:25.138
I figure I'm the best man
for the job.

24:25.172 --> 24:26.205
Yeah? [Slams door]

24:26.240 --> 24:28.508
Well, we'll see about that.

24:28.543 --> 24:30.610
What do you mean,
"maybe next week"?

24:30.645 --> 24:33.980
Man: Excuse me, miss!
Mallory: I need it today!

24:34.014 --> 24:36.982
It's the same order as always.

24:37.050 --> 24:40.619
Okay. Okay, Thursday.
Wonderful.

24:40.654 --> 24:42.688
See you then.
[Phone beeps off]

24:42.756 --> 24:44.156
Bad news?

24:44.223 --> 24:46.792
I don't know
what I'm doing here, Ty.

24:46.860 --> 24:50.596
I had all these options, but
I couldn't make up my mind

24:50.630 --> 24:52.397
so I picked the safe route.

24:52.465 --> 24:57.635
Now I'm stuck here doing the same
thing I've been doing for years.

24:57.703 --> 24:59.771
Well, if you don't want the job,
why don't you just talk to Lou?

24:59.839 --> 25:01.172
And say what?

25:01.239 --> 25:04.642
Thanks for promoting me,
I quit.

25:04.710 --> 25:06.845
No, those aren't the words
that I would use.

25:06.912 --> 25:08.379
It's all Jake's fault.

25:08.447 --> 25:15.285
I mean him going to Paris to work
at a wild west show is amazing

25:15.319 --> 25:18.689
in comparison
to working at Maggie's.

25:18.723 --> 25:22.693
So you and Jake,
after all these years.

25:22.760 --> 25:24.760
You think I like Jake?

25:25.696 --> 25:28.430
Are you kidding?
That's ridiculous.

25:28.499 --> 25:29.665
Yeah, sure.

25:31.568 --> 25:33.335
Everybody used to think
it was the cutest thing -

25:33.403 --> 25:36.038
the little cowboy
with the big crush on mallory

25:36.106 --> 25:38.841
and the way you'd pretend
like you weren't interested.

25:38.909 --> 25:40.976
You guys aren't kids anymore.

25:41.043 --> 25:45.013
Maybe it's time you tell him how you
really feel, one way or the other.

25:46.115 --> 25:49.150
That would be easier
if I knew how I felt.

25:51.020 --> 25:52.654
Amy: Come on! Let's go!

25:52.722 --> 25:53.655
Georgie: Come on!

25:53.723 --> 25:55.089
Amy: [Whistles] Come on!

25:55.157 --> 25:56.224
Georgie: Move it!

25:56.258 --> 25:58.526
Come on, sheep! Go!

25:59.494 --> 26:01.261
[Bleating]

26:01.329 --> 26:03.330
Good job, Georgie.

26:03.398 --> 26:05.298
Just keep 'em from heading off
in the trees.

26:05.333 --> 26:08.002
Georgie: Okay. [Clicks
tongue] Come on, copper.

26:08.036 --> 26:10.004
Lou: Amy! Amy: Hey, Lou!

26:10.071 --> 26:11.138
Lou:
What do you want us to do?

26:11.205 --> 26:12.605
Amy:
Just help keep drivin' 'em.

26:12.640 --> 26:14.440
Lou: All right. Come on, sheep!

26:14.474 --> 26:15.942
Let's move them up here,
Nicole.

26:15.976 --> 26:17.911
Nicole: Come on, sheep!

26:17.945 --> 26:21.280
Lou: Come on, sheep!
Amy: Come on!

26:21.314 --> 26:22.481
Let's go!

26:22.550 --> 26:24.116
Heel! Come on.

26:24.151 --> 26:26.218
Georgie:
Why are they stopping?

26:28.155 --> 26:30.556
Whoa! What's...
What's going on?

26:32.759 --> 26:34.993
It's dad. Dad, no!

26:35.028 --> 26:36.662
There's grandpa!

26:38.297 --> 26:39.731
<i>Grandpa, slow down!</i>

26:41.734 --> 26:43.835
Stop, dad, no!

26:43.870 --> 26:45.536
[Bleating]

26:45.571 --> 26:48.906
Oh no! Oh! Oh! No!

26:48.941 --> 26:50.875
Lou: Easy, Nicole! Oh no!
Whoa, whoa, whoa!

26:50.909 --> 26:52.409
<i>Easy, boy.</i>

26:52.444 --> 26:53.778
<i>Hang on!</i>

26:53.812 --> 26:55.112
Oh! Ungh!

26:55.146 --> 26:56.180
Lou: Nicole!

26:56.214 --> 26:57.281
Ow!

26:59.685 --> 27:01.284
Lou: Nicole!

27:02.252 --> 27:05.455
Nicole, are you all right?

27:05.489 --> 27:07.824
I'm so sorry. Oh...

27:07.858 --> 27:09.325
Amy: Dad, what did you
think you were doing?

27:09.359 --> 27:11.895
Well, I don't know about Jack, but I'm
here to help you with these sheep.

27:11.929 --> 27:13.930
Well, you guys are doing
a great job so far.

27:13.965 --> 27:16.966
Jack: Well, maybe if you'd asked
before setting out like this.

27:17.000 --> 27:19.635
I did ask, and you guys didn't
seem too concerned about it.

27:19.669 --> 27:21.937
Tim: All right, all right,
everybody just calm down.

27:21.972 --> 27:25.040
We'll work together and we'll get
the sheep up to the lease land.

27:25.075 --> 27:26.308
Lou: You know what? I
have a better idea.

27:26.342 --> 27:29.979
How about you two
deal with it yourselves.

27:30.013 --> 27:31.814
[Bleating]

27:31.848 --> 27:33.681
Are you okay
to get back on your horse?

27:33.749 --> 27:35.583
Nicole: I don't know.

27:35.651 --> 27:37.184
Come on, it's all right.

27:37.219 --> 27:38.686
We'll be there the whole time.

27:38.721 --> 27:40.588
<i>Tim: [Whistles] Come
on, sheep, let's go!</i>

27:40.623 --> 27:41.589
<i>Ha!</i>

27:41.657 --> 27:42.690
Okay.

27:43.692 --> 27:46.060
Yeah, okay, I can do it.
All right.

27:47.496 --> 27:48.629
Lou: I'll give you a
leg up, if you want.

27:48.663 --> 27:51.798
You know what?
I think I got it.

27:51.833 --> 27:53.166
All right.

27:54.135 --> 27:55.636
<i>[Bleating]</i>

27:56.604 --> 28:00.573
One, two... Yeah, Nicole!

28:00.642 --> 28:04.277
Okay, next stop, a hot bath
and a cold Pinot grigio.

28:04.311 --> 28:05.645
[Chuckles] Yeah.

28:09.349 --> 28:10.716
Where's Katie?

28:10.784 --> 28:12.484
<i>You were supposed to be</i>
<i>looking after her.</i>

28:12.519 --> 28:13.919
Everything's fine.

28:13.954 --> 28:16.989
Katie's with Ty, at Maggie's.

28:17.057 --> 28:20.992
Yeah, and it turns out it's
perfectly fine to swallow a penny.

28:21.060 --> 28:22.961
She swallowed a penny?

28:23.029 --> 28:24.495
Yeah, Tim's penny.

28:25.464 --> 28:26.765
I don't believe you guys.

28:26.832 --> 28:29.300
<i>Okay, you know what?</i>
<i>I need to get out of here</i>

28:29.334 --> 28:32.137
or I think I'm going
to kill somebody.

28:32.204 --> 28:34.238
Amy: Come on, Georgie.
Tim: Lou...

28:36.908 --> 28:38.308
Really?

28:39.243 --> 28:40.644
[Bleating]

