28:51.589 --> 28:54.390
Hey, Jake,
I'm just closing up.

28:54.424 --> 28:57.026
Yeah, I was wondering
if you'd like a ride home?

28:57.094 --> 28:58.661
You know I have a car, right?

28:58.729 --> 29:02.464
The one parked
right across the street?

29:02.532 --> 29:06.069
Oh yeah, of course.
So... never mind.

29:08.405 --> 29:14.836
- Come on, Jake, what's going on?
- I guess I was hoping that

29:14.944 --> 29:17.112
even if Lou gave you
the job at Maggie's,

29:17.180 --> 29:21.883
you would consider maybe
going to France.

29:21.918 --> 29:24.885
You mean, with you?

29:24.920 --> 29:26.386
Well...

29:27.388 --> 29:29.990
Maybe, yeah..

29:29.992 --> 29:30.925
Meet in Paris,

29:30.992 --> 29:32.927
go visit soraya in London...

29:32.994 --> 29:34.294
Whatever.

29:35.630 --> 29:38.365
I really wish
you would've asked earlier.

29:38.399 --> 29:40.667
I know, I should have.

29:42.937 --> 29:44.804
Stupid idea.

29:44.839 --> 29:49.475
It's not stupid,
it's just bad timing.

29:52.747 --> 29:55.248
Speaking of timing,
I should go.

29:55.282 --> 29:57.616
My flight's tomorrow
and I gotta pack my stuff,

29:57.650 --> 30:02.888
and I guess the reason why I'm
here is just to say goodbye.

30:02.922 --> 30:04.556
Goodbye now?

30:04.590 --> 30:10.495
But if you ever change your mind...
I'm really gonna miss you.

30:11.931 --> 30:15.266
♪ You got a ticket to ride
I'm gonna miss you, too.

30:15.300 --> 30:20.437
♪ Oh, it's not as bad
as it seems ♪

30:21.373 --> 30:25.442
♪ Go...

30:26.378 --> 30:29.913
♪

30:30.848 --> 30:32.849
You remember that time
when I promised

30:32.884 --> 30:36.219
that I was going to take you
on a real date?

30:37.155 --> 30:40.556
Good, 'cause the deal's
still on.

30:40.621 --> 30:43.924
♪ ...the one word you need
to hear most ♪

30:44.828 --> 30:46.796
♪ Go...

30:46.813 --> 30:56.687
♪

31:00.394 --> 31:02.228
<i>Lou: Do you have to leave?</i>

31:02.296 --> 31:04.697
<i>I really wish</i>
<i>you weren't going.</i>

31:04.731 --> 31:07.300
I feel bad, I wanted
everything to be perfect.

31:07.334 --> 31:10.035
Well, I'm not leaving because
everything wasn't perfect,

31:10.070 --> 31:12.838
I'm leaving because it was.

31:12.872 --> 31:15.340
And, uh, what was
the perfect part exactly?

31:15.374 --> 31:17.409
Getting thrown
from a horse or...?

31:17.443 --> 31:20.778
Nicole: No, it was...
I don't know,

31:20.813 --> 31:23.215
getting back on the horse.

31:23.249 --> 31:26.685
It just made me realize
that if I can handle that,

31:26.752 --> 31:29.688
I can handle anything
they throw at me in New York.

31:29.722 --> 31:33.890
I mean, so what if I never get
my broker's license back.

31:33.958 --> 31:37.928
Maybe this is a chance for me
to start over like you did.

31:37.962 --> 31:43.567
Yeah, except I didn't really start
over again, I just came home.

31:44.669 --> 31:47.204
Yeah, well,
when you took me to Maggie's,

31:47.271 --> 31:50.940
that kind of felt like coming
home to me, too, you know?

31:50.974 --> 31:52.174
It made me remember
what it was like

31:52.243 --> 31:55.111
to do a hard day's work,
an honest day's work.

31:55.178 --> 31:56.679
Something real.

31:57.748 --> 32:01.217
I swear, when you hired
mallory, I...

32:01.285 --> 32:02.452
I don't know,

32:02.486 --> 32:05.387
I just wished that
you were actually hiring me.

32:05.455 --> 32:06.821
Right, yeah.

32:06.856 --> 32:09.691
It'd just be a little bit
of a pay cut.

32:12.161 --> 32:14.162
Are-are you serious?

32:14.230 --> 32:19.867
Yeah, I mean... I don't want to take
the job away from mallory, but...

32:23.705 --> 32:26.507
Okay, show the grain to
shiloh, just like before,

32:26.541 --> 32:29.577
and then back away
towards the gate.

32:29.645 --> 32:32.880
Georgie: Here, shiloh,
look what I got you.

32:32.947 --> 32:34.348
You gotta come get it though.

32:34.416 --> 32:36.816
<i>You gotta come get it.</i>

32:36.850 --> 32:38.818
Good boy, shiloh!

32:38.852 --> 32:40.287
[Gate clunks and creaks open]

32:41.255 --> 32:43.323
Good boy...

32:43.357 --> 32:44.658
Okay.

32:44.725 --> 32:46.025
<i>Amy: That's good.</i>

32:46.059 --> 32:48.695
Now put the bucket down by pogey
and then walk away.

32:54.033 --> 32:56.769
Okay, go ahead,
you can have it.

32:56.803 --> 32:58.103
[Snorts]

33:01.240 --> 33:13.685
♪

33:13.719 --> 33:15.119
[Happy laugh]

33:21.860 --> 33:25.529
[Sniffing and snorting]

33:25.563 --> 33:26.797
Okay, guys.

33:29.667 --> 33:39.142
♪

33:39.176 --> 33:40.509
Here you go.

33:40.544 --> 33:41.744
Thank you,
this looks really good.

33:41.778 --> 33:43.912
Good, good. Enjoy.

33:43.947 --> 33:45.280
Thanks.

33:46.216 --> 33:49.685
How's Katie? Katie is fine.

33:49.720 --> 33:52.488
Um, but you know we're just
still waiting, so...

33:53.623 --> 33:58.226
Uh, mallory, do you remember
when you first told me

33:58.260 --> 34:00.729
you wanted this manager job
and I...

34:00.763 --> 34:03.565
And I said I didn't think
you were manager material?

34:03.599 --> 34:06.000
It's funny how wrong
someone can be, isn't it?

34:06.034 --> 34:07.034
Right.

34:07.069 --> 34:10.170
Well, yes, but um...

34:10.205 --> 34:12.806
Also, you know,
I know I gave you the job

34:12.841 --> 34:18.078
and you are really good at
it - you are - but um...

34:18.112 --> 34:20.714
I just can't help but thinking,
you know, you are young

34:20.748 --> 34:25.252
and you have a whole year off, you
should just go and do something crazy.

34:25.286 --> 34:28.755
Be adventurous.
Try something new!

34:28.822 --> 34:30.623
Lou, are you firing me?

34:30.690 --> 34:34.260
Mallory, okay, please,
it's not like that.

34:34.327 --> 34:35.495
Okay.

34:35.562 --> 34:38.030
I promise I didn't make
any kind of commitment,

34:38.063 --> 34:42.234
but I was just talking to Nicole
in like a blue sky sort of way,

34:42.302 --> 34:47.972
and I sort of offered her the job and
she sort of said she would consider it.

34:48.040 --> 34:50.308
You gave Nicole my job?

34:51.243 --> 34:54.212
Lou! Thank you!

34:54.280 --> 34:56.347
Thank you so much!

34:56.416 --> 34:58.717
This is what I was hoping for.

34:58.785 --> 35:01.652
Mallory, I thought this job was
exactly what you were hoping for?

35:01.720 --> 35:09.092
It was, I swear, until I got it, and
then I was just too afraid to tell you.

35:09.160 --> 35:12.329
So you just let me tie myself up in
knots trying to let you down easy?

35:12.397 --> 35:17.500
Yeah, and you did a great job
- I mean, doing me a favour

35:17.568 --> 35:20.269
and firing me
at the same time.

35:20.337 --> 35:22.772
Lou, it was perfect.

35:25.242 --> 35:26.943
[Truck rumbles up]

35:28.512 --> 35:30.480
[Sheep bleat]

35:31.448 --> 35:33.381
Jack!

35:33.450 --> 35:35.584
Surprised to see you here.

35:35.652 --> 35:36.685
What're you doing?

35:36.719 --> 35:37.953
Counting sheep.

35:38.020 --> 35:40.221
Just want to make sure
we got 'em all.

35:40.289 --> 35:41.623
I didn't know you cared.

35:41.691 --> 35:42.758
I care plenty.

35:42.792 --> 35:48.028
At the price you paid for
them, you caught my interest.

35:48.096 --> 35:49.430
I can't believe
what I'm hearing.

35:49.465 --> 35:51.833
So you're saying that
I did something right;

35:51.867 --> 35:53.233
That we're all good now?

35:53.268 --> 35:56.103
Yeah, things worked out
just the way I'd hoped.

35:56.137 --> 35:58.539
<i>Tim: Yeah, well, the only part
I can't figure is that...</i>

35:58.574 --> 36:00.007
I bought the sheep,
they're on my land,

36:00.041 --> 36:02.777
so I don't know where you
fit into the equation.

36:02.845 --> 36:05.345
Well, do the math, Tim.

36:05.379 --> 36:09.115
See, these sheep, <i>they're mine
now, lock, stock, and barrel.</i>

36:09.149 --> 36:10.851
They were my investment,
completely.

36:10.885 --> 36:11.852
They were my idea.

36:11.886 --> 36:15.321
Ideas are cheap unlike vet
bills and supplements,

36:15.356 --> 36:16.923
and the grazing fees
you owe me.

36:16.958 --> 36:18.358
Grazing fees?
You take a look around, buddy.

36:18.425 --> 36:20.058
You wanna talk about grazing fees?
Not to mention

36:20.126 --> 36:22.795
the constant headache I've had
since you dumped them on me.

36:22.829 --> 36:24.797
Tim: I never had a headache
while you were in Arizona.

36:24.831 --> 36:26.231
Jack:
You think my time's free?

36:26.265 --> 36:27.666
Tim: Nothing with you is free.

36:27.701 --> 36:30.636
Jack: Chasing these miserable critters
around every day since they got here.

36:30.704 --> 36:32.337
[Bleating]

36:33.272 --> 36:34.974
Tim: The little one's cute.

36:41.847 --> 36:44.382
Okay, we should get going.

36:44.416 --> 36:45.649
Just give it one more minute.

36:45.717 --> 36:48.452
I just want to make sure
we're not rushing things.

36:56.161 --> 36:58.929
I'd say so far, so good. Yeah.

37:01.265 --> 37:04.167
Oh wait, he's looking
for his mom.

37:06.603 --> 37:08.604
Just don't move.

37:17.147 --> 37:18.680
<i>Oh, good.</i>

37:18.714 --> 37:20.649
<i>Ty: He looks like he's
made himself at home.</i>

37:22.452 --> 37:29.525
♪

37:29.527 --> 37:37.131
♪

37:37.166 --> 37:38.866
All right, I'm gonna go.

37:38.900 --> 37:40.234
Okay.

37:40.269 --> 37:41.936
Thank you.

37:42.871 --> 37:44.605
See you later.

37:50.278 --> 37:53.113
Well, let's go.

37:56.551 --> 37:58.851
You all right, Georgie?

37:58.919 --> 38:03.722
Well, I already miss Bobby Jean and I'm
really gonna miss shiloh when he goes.

38:03.790 --> 38:05.824
I warned you
not to get too attached.

38:05.892 --> 38:10.629
And I tried, but I don't know how you
stand it, always saying goodbye.

38:10.697 --> 38:12.898
It's just part
of the horse business.

38:12.966 --> 38:14.900
But you know what
the good thing is?

38:14.968 --> 38:18.370
You get to say hello just as
often as you say goodbye,

38:18.438 --> 38:21.672
so it kind of balances out,
right?

38:21.740 --> 38:23.108
[Chuckles]

38:24.610 --> 38:26.444
<i>[Door shuts]</i>

38:26.512 --> 38:27.878
Hey, Jack.

38:27.946 --> 38:29.647
What will it be? Coffee? Pie?

38:29.715 --> 38:32.817
No, what I'd really like
is a stiff drink,

38:32.884 --> 38:36.920
but I guess I'll settle
for coffee, decaf.

38:39.357 --> 38:41.992
Don't get too used to this
personalized service.

38:42.059 --> 38:43.427
It's my last day.

38:44.462 --> 38:45.762
Really?

38:45.830 --> 38:47.531
Well, I'm sorry to hear that.

38:47.599 --> 38:49.299
What's your plan?

38:49.334 --> 38:50.534
Not too sure.

38:51.502 --> 38:56.672
I mean, my track record in big life
decisions hasn't been too good lately.

38:57.641 --> 39:00.876
I mean,
what if I screw up again?

39:00.944 --> 39:04.880
Make a bad decision, do something
stupid that I'm gonna regret

39:04.914 --> 39:07.349
for the rest of my life?

39:07.416 --> 39:09.984
Mallory,
everybody's got regrets.

39:10.919 --> 39:12.887
But here's the thing.

39:12.955 --> 39:18.160
When you get to my age, you realize
that what you end up regretting

39:18.194 --> 39:23.397
aren't the things you did, they're
the things you didn't do.

39:24.732 --> 39:29.270
So you're saying I should go
to Paris with Jake?

39:30.938 --> 39:34.041
Paris with Jake?

39:34.075 --> 39:35.876
It's not what you think.

39:35.910 --> 39:38.812
We're friends, buddies, bff's.

39:38.846 --> 39:43.916
Well, it might be that way right now,
but things can change, you know,

39:43.950 --> 39:48.688
especially when you're
thousands of Miles from home.

39:48.722 --> 39:52.925
But if things are gonna change,
they're gonna change here

39:52.959 --> 39:56.528
just as much
as they will in Europe.

39:58.898 --> 40:03.402
There's still a seat
available on Jake's flight.

40:03.436 --> 40:10.342
♪ Everything's changing ♪ but nothing
is new ♪ and I've been wondering...

40:10.376 --> 40:14.545
Oh, I must be getting soft
in my old age.

40:14.580 --> 40:19.917
♪ How to believe what are you doing
here serving me coffee then?

40:19.951 --> 40:23.854
♪ I've been wondering

40:24.789 --> 40:28.592
Jack, I'm gonna miss you most
out of everybody.

40:31.596 --> 40:36.433
♪ We're all wondering I'm
gonna miss you, too.

